~DeL jumped to her feet and rolled up her scrolls, it was late, very late, and she too needed sleep. Crawling into her bed, Lukoi jumped up and lay at the bottom by her fett, snuggling like a little boy. She was glad Solari had come home, Solari was one of the elders, one of the first she had met those many years ago when she first came to Themiscrya, Solari was a true amazon.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=solariwolf>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(7/17/02 8:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A True Amazon</span><hr size=1> ~Solari awoke the next day, rested and happy. She was grateful to whomever kept her hut in working condition. She had not expected to find it in such good order. She knew she would be facing many questions now that the village was awake...and she was ready to answer them. Solari held in her possession many an item from her travels in the lands outside the known amazon lands. She knows she has missed out on alot during her travels and will eventually be brought back up to speed on what has been happening with her fellow amazon sisters. Solari sits in her hut, going thru the many scrolls she has written and items she brought back in order to present to her old friend and queen, Hippolyte. Thoughts began to swim in her mind of how her old friend would re-act to her return, and of how her other sisters would be upon her silent return. Soon Solari would not have to wonder anymore, she dressed in her usual amazon attire, placed her sword on her back and gathered a small bag full of goodies for the queen, 