 &quot;Ok, Del, you can throw a small celebration. I guess this means I have to dress up.&quot; And she giggled softly.<br>
~Solari grabbed her boots and headed for her hut. She needed to get a few things taken care of and wanted to take a long ride through the valley before the celebration. Solari changed into dryer clothes and mounted up on her horse and headed down a forest path towards the valley.~  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=solariwolf>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#993300>(8/18/02 8:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A quiet ride</span><hr size=1> ~Solari urged her mare into a canter and enjoyed the fresh air and wind in her face. She rode through the forest, down paths she hadnt been on since she left the villiage so long ago. She rode past the waterfall she used to frequent, towards her old cabin she had built for herself and her first love and the mother of her child. The cabin had long since burnt down, but the bare spot and some old founding posts still stood. <br>
 Solari pulled her mare up and just looked at the spot where she and her wife, DeianeiraW called home. Instantly she was flooded with memories of past times when she was happy and in love. That marriage brought two wonderful daughters into the amazon nation. Daughters she left with Terrayus when she left the village when her wife died. Solari had not been as happy as she was when she was with her love, but she did love. <br>
 She frowned slightly and turned her mare back towards the vlliage. Reminders of the past was something Solari didnt want to think about. She was home and her life was starting anew as it always seemed to do when she was back in Themiscrya. She was ready to settle down again, her family needed her and her heart had mended it wounds.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazoncyane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>amazoncyane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#993300>(8/26/02 6:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quiet ride</span><hr size=1> Wen Solari got back, Cyane met her as she dismounted &quot;Solari, I have heard many things about you.  Please come with me, I wish to talk with you about some things&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=solariwolf>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#993300>(8/26/02 6:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quiet ride</span><hr size=1> ~Solari brushed back her two small braids as the unfamiliar amazon met her. She patted her horse for the nice ride as she watched the amazon before her speak. <br>
 &quot; Who are you and just what do you known about me?&quot; Solari didn't mean to sound harsh. But years of traveling had made her weary of strangers who knew her by name and didn't identify themselves, even if they were amazons. <br>
 She began to unsaddle her horse while the amazon explained herself. ~<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazoncyane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>amazoncyane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#993300>(8/26/02 8:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Explaining one's self</span><hr size=1> &quot;I am Cyane, and I have wished to become an amazon, but to no avail.  I have even prayed to Artemis, that didn't help either.  Others, for one reason or another, are suspicious of me, except for Velaska, who hates me.&quot;<br>
&quot;I know that the others call you a 'true amazon', therefore you must be well versed in their ways, which one day I hope to learn.&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=solariwolf>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#993300>(8/26/02 10:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=371.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Explaining one's self</span><hr size=1> ~Solari listened closely to what the young amazon was saying before replying. She placed the saddle on the post beside her horse, then turned to her.<br>
 &quot; Well Cyane.. I am a true amazon and know the ways very well....but if the others have their suspicions, then something must have been placed there to give them their doubts. Becoming an amazon isn't an easy task. They can be quite harsh in their judgements. Newcomers are at great risk for that. Sometimes they dont make the cut the first time around, sometimes they have to find another tribe willing to let them in....it's never easy when you are a amazon...&quot;<br>
 Solari finished brushing her horse, then sat down in the wooden chair by her hut. She let what she had said sink in a little before finishing her thought to the young Cyane.<br>
 &quot; I know not why the others are suspicious of you, I haven't been home long enough to get every detail of things. But my advice is to give it some time, be patient and accept whatever the answer is on wanting to become a member. Like i mentioned earlier...becoming an amazon isnt easy, and praying to the gods and goddesses, well, let's just say that sometimes they dont answer us in the way we like at times.&quot; <br>
 She looked at the amazon and took in a deep breath. She fiddled with the sole of her boot as she proped her leg up. <br>
 &quot;That is all I can offer to you at this time. Take it from someone who knows. Be patient and learn to accept what comes your way, whether you agree with it or not. &quot;<br>
